# AgToosa Build Rules

When executing `/agtoosa-build` or any implementation work, follow `Docs/AgToosa_Build.md` precisely.

## Key constraints

- **Red before Green** — the failing test MUST exist before any implementation code is written.
- **Atomic tasks** — break the spec into the smallest independently testable units before coding.
- **No file > 500 lines** — refactor immediately if a file approaches the limit.
- Run SAST/DAST (Semgrep, CodeQL, Gitleaks) after each task, not just at the end.
- Report **Terminal Evidence Contract** fields for every command and parallel subagent; unresolved exits or warnings block checkbox completion.
- If build prerequisites fail, **stop** and instruct the user — do **not** auto-run `/agtoosa-spec`.
- Update `Docs/Master-Plan.md` Active Tasks checkboxes and Update Log as tasks complete.
- On successful completion, print this line verbatim: `✅ Done. Run /agtoosa-status to verify findings cleared.`
